#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:15
msgid "**out**"
msgstr "**out**"

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:-1
msgid "ndarray, None, or tuple of ndarray and None, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:12
msgid ""
"A location into which the result is stored. If provided, it must have a "
"shape that the inputs broadcast to. If not provided or None, a freshly-"
"allocated array is returned. A tuple (possible only as a keyword argument) "
"must have length equal to the number of outputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:23
msgid "**where**"
msgstr "**where**"

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:-1
msgid "array_like, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:18
msgid ""
"This condition is broadcast over the input. At locations where the condition "
"is True, the `out` array will be set to the ufunc result. Elsewhere, the "
"`out` array will retain its original value. Note that if an uninitialized "
"`out` array is created via the default ``out=None``, locations within it "
"where the condition is False will remain uninitialized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:29
msgid "**\\*\\*kwargs**"
msgstr "**\\*\\*kwargs**"

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:26
msgid ""
"For other keyword-only arguments, see the :ref:`ufunc docs <ufuncs.kwargs>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr "回傳值"

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:42
msgid "**y**"
msgstr "**y**"

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:-1
msgid "ndarray, bool"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:34
msgid ""
"True where ``x`` is not positive infinity, negative infinity, or NaN; false "
"otherwise. This is a scalar if `x` is a scalar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:47
msgid ":obj:`isinf`, :obj:`isneginf`, :obj:`isposinf`, :obj:`isnan`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:51
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:52
msgid ""
"Not a Number, positive infinity and negative infinity are considered to be "
"non-finite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.isfinite:55
msgid ""
"NumPy uses the IEEE Standard for Binary Floating-Point for Arithmetic (IEEE "
"754). This means that Not a Number is not equivalent to infinity. Also that "
"positive infinity is not equivalent to negative infinity. But infinity is "
"equivalent to positive infinity.  Errors result if the second argument is "
"also supplied when `x` is a scalar input, or if first and second arguments "
"have different shapes."
msgstr ""

